commit.message: Merge commit 'fix-utilities' into master

Fix physics roll

Cleanup commit 5ac56d8eb161 introduced a local cache of a variable that
may be updated by a call to `set_object_turnroll`.  The local cache was
not updated, causing use of the cached variable later in the function to
produce an incorrect result.  Fix this by rereading the variable from
the authoritative source after the call to `set_object_turnroll`.
Reduce the scope of the initial cache to reflect the limited scope in
which use of the cached variable is valid.

Fixes: 5ac56d8eb161194aa46058d3bf0ab32e4267fb35 ("Reduce scope of vms_angvec local variables")
Reported-by: ziplantil <https://github.com/dxx-rebirth/dxx-rebirth/issues/766>

Add type annotations to SConstruct
Fix comment about which bot is killed
Simplify valptridx::ptridx inheritance of `index_type`

Rename valptridx reference_type to reference

Match the name used for C++ iterator_traits, for better interoperability
with the standard library.

Rename valptridx pointer_type to pointer

Match the name used for C++ iterator_traits, for better interoperability
with the standard library.

Use CTAD for segment object iteration

- Remove the helper function `objects_in`.
- Rename `segment_object_range_t` to `objects_in`.
- Add an explicit deduction guide, since the template type cannot be
  deduced from the constructor arguments.
Expand vm_vec_zero inline

Remove support for drawing terrain outline

The control variable was made `static` in 2014 (commit
d9a3bf5a57d733d57ee5ec0593d0dec451ca7779), and the compiler has been
optimizing it to a constant false, so no one can enable it.  No one has
ever reported this as a problem.  Remove support for drawing the
outline.

Move LOCKED_PITCH_FACTOR into kconfig.cpp

It is only used in one function.  Make it a static constexpr in the
function that uses it.

Simplify testing vector equality

Prefer vms_vector::operator== over explicitly checking each member
individually.
Reduce lifetime of vm_vec_sub results

Rework countarray storage

- Choose the size_type based on the maximum value it may need to store,
  rather than defaulting to `unsigned`
- Add `constexpr` where practical
- Use `std::next()` to advance iterators
- Make `destroy` static, since it did not need access to member variables
- Make `destroy` run last-to-first instead of first-to-last
- Make `destroy` empty for trivially destructible types
Use defaulted constructor for array_base_count_type if >=gcc-13
Add valgrind wrappers for unsigned variants of PHYSFSX read helpers
Use std::ranges to process song filenames
Make `PHYSFSX_fgets` return a `std::span` describing the read bytes

Fix `PHYSFSX_fgets` when read boundary ends on "\r"

`PHYSFSX_fgets` treats any of "\r", "\n", or "\r\n" as a line
terminator.  When the length of the line is such that `PHYSFSX_fgets`
places a '\r' in the last element, the prior logic would advance `p` to
point to `e`.  The subsequent call to `PHYSFS_seek` would then advance
by `p - e + 1` => `e - e + 1` => `1`.  However, the byte skipped over by
that `1` may or may not be a newline.  If it is not, then the first byte
of the following line is skipped and never seen by the caller.  Change
the test so that a "\r" in the last element leaves `p` pointing at the
"\r", so that `PHYSFS_seek` advances by `(e - 1) + e + 1` => `0`, which
leaves the unread byte to be returned by the next call to
`PHYSFSX_fgets`.
Normalize ui_pad_read test of PHYSFSX_fgets result

Simplify PHYSFSX_fgets_t::get return paths

Reorder the exit logic so that a single exit can always perform cleanup
without requiring a helper function.  This should not change the behavior
of the function, but may generate better code.

Use std::ranges::equal to compare netgame strings to candidates

The defined names have known lengths and are known not to contain internal
null terminators, so use std::ranges::equal instead of strncmp.

Use std::ranges::equal to compare config strings to candidates

The defined names have known lengths and are known not to contain internal
null terminators, so use std::ranges::equal instead of strncmp.
Tighten range constraints on zip

Replace cast_range_result with std::ranges::equal_range

Use std::ranges::equal_range with a projection function instead of
defining a special iterator to convert the result of `operator*`.  This
avoids the need to make iterator_result_converter satisfy the concept
for an iterator.

Add test for Class Template Argument Deduction

CTAD is already used in Rebirth code.  Add a test to reject compilers
which do not support it.  Include in the test a construct known to cause
gcc-11 to reject the code, since that construct already exists in the
game code, and thus gcc-11 cannot compile the game.  This test forces
a build using gcc-11 to fail early, at the configure stage, rather than
only failing when it reaches the header that uses a user defined
deduction guide for an inner class.

Attempt appending architecture to output

vLKp note: due to an out-of-order cherry-pick, one hunk from the
original commit was dropped, as it depends on a commit not yet merged.
The original commit is 950a43bbfa87ddf650a87bdb420cb0bf05b92e5c.
Actually use GCC 13

Use hard links when staging files for Windows zip construction

This avoids unnecessary copies.

Use hard links when staging files for appimage construction

This avoids unnecessary copies, and may enable the appimage tool to
recognize duplicate files and store them as hard links in the appimage
bundle.
